# Introduction {#introduction}

* ## What is it {#what-is-it}

  * Play as a flower-faced shop merchant providing art supplies to a town full of creative bees. Manage the shop's inventory, cash flow, employees, and even a small side-business, as each day progress in 3-minute intervals.  
    * Customers of various art disciplines will require the materials of their trade, ranging from simple pencils and charcoals, to marble sculptures architectural models...even model hobbyists have their place on the shelves\!  
    * Employees can help manage the burden, but will come with their own costs as each one has a different salary. However by carefully managing their breaks and shifts you can balance out the labor. They also have different specialties and talents so experiment with the crew that works best for you.  
    * An upcoming update will feature a new gameplay mechanic for the player to try, to add a sort of "survival/exploration" mode. I am very excited to star that, but for now that's all I can say\!

  * ## Who made it {#who-made-it}

    * SalamancaTech with the help of AI agents such as Gemini and Jules.

  * ## How to play it {#how-to-play-it}

    * Start by choosing your game type (for a new player I recommend "Standard Unlocks" with "No Market" and "Continuous Day" turned OFF)  
    * Open the phone UI and begin by selecting which materials you'd like to sell, and then purchase some inventory. While you are here you can assign the shelves or do it manually when unloading the dock.  
    * Unload the supplies from the dock to the shelf for customers to access. Note: Your basket can only hold 5 items at a time, the contents of which can be reviewed in the button above.  
    * Customers will automatically filter in once the shop opens (green part of the pie-clock) and either retrieve the items themselves, or request assistance in some way, and then approach the counter where they can be charged.  
    * Supplies can be bought at any point so keep an eye on your inventory as well as customer demands.  
    * Eventually the day will come to an end and any remaining customers will finish their purchases and leave, or if they are unhappy they will just leave. There is one final part to the day cycle which is closing time, allowing you to purchase items for the following day, unlock new parts to the store (new art styles, more shelves, employees, or even a whole new part of the business), unload the loading dock, and more.  
    * When the clock reaches "midnight" the day has ended and a final report will appear, showing you the sales made, the bills accrued, the market changes (if applicable) and more. Use this time to plan for the next day's events, when you are ready, press "Start Next Day"  
    * Remember that there are weekly bills that will be charged every 7 days and if you are unable to pay it, that will be game over\! Consider hiring employees, offering a larger variety of art supplies, and invest in a side business to increase the profits made; however, keep in mind that each of these will come with their own costs as well, including daily salaries.  
    * Have fun and see how far you can get before the bees (or maybe something else) overwhelms\!

  * ## What’s to Come {#what’s-to-come}

    * Here is where I will put my roadmap, (or maybe a link to the roadmap) but for now I will leave it simplistic.  
    * Transference of code to Godot engine for ease of correction and expansion.  
    * Fully working Markets (the mainly stable ones are "Off" and "Daily Mood", the others work but haven't been as rigorously tested so that will be done to ensure they are stable)  
    * "Items for sale" will be one-time purchases that will alter the artists' abilities and purchases  
    * Survival Mode- an optional "after the shop closes" level where the player goes home. There will be obstacles, places to explore, supplies or "items for sale" to find, and an enemy.  
    * Much more, but until I get a proper roadmap, this is what I've got to share.
